content.content: Hey frens, This is the first post in the lounge category.  Not sure if its the right place, but it seems I’m not sure where this would fit in the other categories (edit: moving to the public goods funding category now). Anywho, I am a big data nerd, and I wanted to surface some of our internal dashboards of round over round stats for Gitcoin Grants.  This data provides our best view on the history of the growth of Gitcoin Grants round over round, but I cant guarantee it with 100% accuracy.   Round Over Round  Screen Shot 2021-07-01 at 2.09.51 PM3534×1286 343 KB  See these stats live on $61.9m in Results | Gitcoin  Round 10  photo_2021-07-02 11.39.392560×1227 187 KB   Round 9  Screen Shot 2021-07-01 at 2.07.58 PM3486×1676 435 KB   Round 8  Screen Shot 2021-07-01 at 2.07.50 PM3510×1686 427 KB   Round 7  Screen Shot 2021-07-01 at 2.07.42 PM3500×1688 441 KB   Round 6  Screen Shot 2021-07-01 at 2.07.34 PM3504×1690 437 KB   Round 5  Screen Shot 2021-07-01 at 2.07.27 PM3508×1682 461 KB   Round 4  Screen Shot 2021-07-01 at 2.07.16 PM3498×1678 446 KB   Round 3  Screen Shot 2021-07-01 at 2.07.08 PM3508×1696 475 KB   Round 2  Screen Shot 2021-07-01 at 2.06.42 PM3496×1678 460 KB   Round 1  Screen Shot 2021-07-01 at 2.06.30 PM3478×1692 426 KB
Just about 15% growth in the number of contributors from round 9 to round 10. We are growing at a significant rate.
